me to thank you.
She's happy you're here.

704
00:40:19.767 --> 00:40:22.251
You... You didn't
tell her all about...

705
00:40:22.320 --> 00:40:24.160
No. I told her
you had the flu.

706
00:40:25.273 --> 00:40:27.089
(LAUGHS) That's good.

707
00:40:31.229 --> 00:40:32.295
So we're gonna do this?

708
00:40:36.084 --> 00:40:38.768
We're gonna
take down Bryce?
Yeah.

709
00:40:39.787 --> 00:40:40.803
We are.

710
00:40:40.871 --> 00:40:42.388
(RETCHES)

711
00:40:43.324 --> 00:40:44.324
JUSTIN: Ugh!

712
00:40:44.959 --> 00:40:48.043
In 72 to 96 hours.

713
00:40:49.648 --> 00:40:53.315
I thought maybe the sign
in my yard was just
about my dad's campaign.

714
00:40:53.384 --> 00:40:56.886
But somebody is targeting me.
MR. PORTER: That's terrible.

715
00:40:58.773 --> 00:41:01.124
And you have no idea
who might have done it?

716
00:41:02.677 --> 00:41:03.760
No.

717
00:41:03.828 --> 00:41:06.645
You can't think of anyone
you may have hurt?

718
00:41:06.714 --> 00:41:12.401
Or anyone that may have...
A reason not to like you?

719
00:41:13.554 --> 00:41:16.172
Hey. I'm...
I'm the victim here.

720
00:41:16.240 --> 00:41:19.058
Marcus. let me. uh.
ask you something.

721
00:41:19.127 --> 00:41:21.611
Your father.
he's a churchgoing man. right?

722
00:41:22.296 --> 00:41:23.713
Yeah.

723
00:41:23.782 --> 00:41:26.482
What do you think he would say
if he listened to your tape?

724
00:41:27.969 --> 00:41:31.003
(SCOFFS) What would your wife
say if she listened to yours?

725
00:41:31.072 --> 00:41:34.807
Oh. I already told
my wife everything.

726
00:41:37.195 --> 00:41:39.845
And I've taken a long.
hard look in the mirror.

727
00:41:41.149 --> 00:41:42.149
Have you?

728
00:41:45.787 --> 00:41:47.553
Just find out who did this.

729
00:41:47.622 --> 00:41:52.007
Marcus. I am on borrowed time
here at Liberty and I know it.

730
00:41:52.076 --> 00:41:54.227
But as long as I am here.

731
00:41:54.296 --> 00:41:57.563
I'm gonna make sure
that the kids who actually
need my help get it.

732
00:41:57.632 --> 00:42:01.016
And those that need
something else?
That they get that. too.

733
00:42:16.985 --> 00:42:18.217
Holy shit.

734
00:42:19.520 --> 00:42:21.432
Tyler. I thought
you were talking
about BB guns.

735
00:42:21.456 --> 00:42:22.955
What do you use these for?

736
00:42:24.142 --> 00:42:26.558
TYLER: Just. you know.
shooting cans and stuff.

737
00:42:27.845 --> 00:42:29.945
But if you don't want to
try it. we don't have to.

738
00:42:30.014 --> 00:42:31.974
Oh. hell yeah. I want to try it!

739
00:42:33.318 --> 00:42:35.184
You have to teach me
how to do it.

740
00:42:36.421 --> 00:42:39.188
Yeah. of course.
Here. just let me.

741
00:42:48.366 --> 00:42:52.201
This one's got a bit of
a kick to it. Okay?
So just be ready for it.

742
00:42:55.506 --> 00:42:57.840
Yeah. hold the gun
with your dominant hand.

743
00:42:57.909 --> 00:43:00.944
Keep your finger outside. okay?

744
00:43:01.012 --> 00:43:02.545
Until you're ready to shoot.

745
00:43:02.614 --> 00:43:06.115
Use your other hand
to cradle the gun underneath.
it keeps it steady.

746
00:43:06.184 --> 00:43:07.850
This shit's heavy. (LAUGHS)

747
00:43:11.222 --> 00:43:12.888
CYRUS: Like that?
TYLER: Yeah.

748
00:43:12.957 --> 00:43:14.857
Safety?
Yeah.

749
00:43:17.194 --> 00:43:18.227
Pick a target.

750
00:43:19.631 --> 00:43:22.765
And when you're ready.
okay. turn the safety off...

751
00:43:26.120 --> 00:43:27.587
Put your finger
on the trigger...

752
00:43:29.758 --> 00:43:31.557
And squeeze your hands
together like this.

753
00:43:39.267 --> 00:43:41.200
Ha! Woo!

754
00:43:42.370 --> 00:43:43.370
Woo!

755
00:43:55.716 --> 00:44:00.202
He thinks he can just
walk in here. giving me
advice about Jackie.

756
00:44:00.271 --> 00:44:02.722
the trial. after everything
he's put me through?

757
00:44:04.158 --> 00:44:06.809
I'm sorry.
But again.
maybe he has a point.

758
00:44:08.746 --> 00:44:11.347
Think I had this fantasy
that I was going

759
00:44:12.750 --> 00:44:15.868
to tell Hannah's story
to the world.

760
00:44:15.936 --> 00:44:19.805
Make them understand.
Certainly aren't
getting it in court.

761
00:44:21.042 --> 00:44:22.042
No.

762
00:44:25.363 --> 00:44:26.643
Although. Jessica...

763
00:44:29.517 --> 00:44:31.684
I think she did her best.
Don't you?

764
00:44:33.170 --> 00:44:35.104
Yeah. Yeah.

765
00:44:36.524 --> 00:44:37.524
I think she did.

766
00:44:39.544 --> 00:44:41.522
She's the girl on the tape.
isn't she. Tony?

767
00:44:41.546 --> 00:44:44.647
She's the one on tape nine?
Is she afraid of Bryce Walker?

768
00:44:44.716 --> 00:44:47.093
Is she afraid no one will
believe her? Why won't
she come forward?

769
00:44:47.117 --> 00:44:50.602
Yeah. I have to ask you.
Why do you need her to?

770
00:44:50.671 --> 00:44:52.466
She only knows
what happened to her.

771
00:44:52.490 --> 00:44:53.800
she doesn't know
what happened to Hannah.

772
00:44:53.824 --> 00:44:56.808
'Cause Hannah isn't here to
speak to what happened to her.

773
00:44:56.877 --> 00:44:59.911
I mean. you're right.
it may or may not help
our case against the school.

774
00:44:59.980 --> 00:45:04.016
But Tony. it could help build
a criminal case against Bryce.

775
00:45:07.188 --> 00:45:10.222
The cops. they already
have the tapes.

776
00:45:10.291 --> 00:45:11.557
They won't act on anything

777
00:45:11.626 --> 00:45:15.227
unless they have a living
victim to tell her story.

778
00:45:15.296 --> 00:45:17.580
And it's gotta come out
in court?

779
00:45:17.648 --> 00:45:23.735
Dennis says we need
a witness who can speak
to a pattern of behavior.

780
00:45:24.705 --> 00:45:27.506
It could lead
to an arrest. Tony.

781
00:45:28.693 --> 00:45:31.928
Bryce needs to pay
for what he did to Hannah.

782
00:45:31.996 --> 00:45:35.364
to Jessica. to who knows
how many other girls.

783
00:45:36.217 --> 00:45:37.766
I want it to come out.

784
00:45:37.835 --> 00:45:41.437
In court.
in a sheriff's office.
I don't care where.

785
00:45:43.074 --> 00:45:46.192
And Jessica is the only one
who can speak to
what happened that night.

786
00:45:50.097 --> 00:45:51.137
And Justin.

787
00:45:53.117 --> 00:45:54.216
Do you know where he is?

788
00:45:55.603 --> 00:45:57.981
I can ask around for him again.

789
00:45:58.005 --> 00:46:01.405
I mean. I have a friend
who might be able
to track him down.

790
00:46:04.061 --> 00:46:05.101
I'm sorry. okay?

791
00:46:05.162 --> 00:46:06.406
DEPUTY STANDALL:
Sorry isn't gonna cut it.

792
00:46:06.430 --> 00:46:08.864
You haven't even been back
less than a week

793
00:46:08.933 --> 00:46:10.093
and you're already
skipping school.

794
00:46:10.117 --> 00:46:12.534
MRS. STANDALL: Okay. Bill.
every 17-year-old kid

795
00:46:12.603 --> 00:46:15.237
skips a couple of classes
now and then.

796
00:46:15.306 --> 00:46:18.035
DEPUTY STANDALL: Well. if he's
ever gonna be a normal
17-year-old kid again.

797
00:46:18.059 --> 00:46:19.603
he's gotta put in the work.
that's all.

798
00:46:19.627 --> 00:46:20.971
I'm sorry I'm not
fucking normal!

799
00:46:20.995 --> 00:46:23.007
MRS. STANDALL: Language!
I know that's hard for you.

800
00:46:23.031 --> 00:46:25.191
DEPUTY STANDALL:
That's not what
I'm talking about. kid!

801
00:46:26.367 --> 00:46:27.633
Alex!

802
00:46:27.701 --> 00:46:29.135
(FOOTSTEPS LEAVING)

803
00:46:31.939 --> 00:46:34.073
Honey.
(SIGHS)

804
00:46:34.142 --> 00:46:37.026
You need to ease up on him.
He's trying. okay?

805
00:46:37.095 --> 00:46:40.379
Well. he needs to try harder.
'Cause he's got to get better.

806
00:46:41.916 --> 00:46:43.215
He has to get better.

807
00:46:44.552 --> 00:46:46.001
If he doesn't...

808
00:46:47.772 --> 00:46:50.322
If this is as far as he gets.

809
00:46:50.391 --> 00:46:52.491
you've got to stop
blaming yourself.

810
00:46:52.560 --> 00:46:53.576
Why?

811
00:46:54.411 --> 00:46:55.611
It was my gun.

812
00:47:02.353 --> 00:47:03.353
(EXHALES)

813
00:47:05.589 --> 00:47:07.890
Fuck! Fuck!

814
00:47:07.959 --> 00:47:09.091
(GRUNTS)

815
00:47:10.862 --> 00:47:12.494
(PANTING)

816
00:47:23.808 --> 00:47:25.924
(SOBS)

817
00:47:44.445 --> 00:47:45.725
Come on. Clay.

818
00:47:54.872 --> 00:47:56.671
(SOBS)

819
00:47:56.740 --> 00:47:59.007
MARCUS: <i>Too many kids
still feel powerless.</i>

820
00:48:31.609 --> 00:48:32.609
Jesus.

821
00:48:37.215 --> 00:48:40.149
Marcus Cole turned
into a nice surprise today.
didn't he?

822
00:48:40.218 --> 00:48:42.763
Yeah. I am not sure
why Dennis thought
he would be good for them.

823
00:48:42.787 --> 00:48:44.503
with that kind of story to tell.

824
00:48:44.572 --> 00:48:47.772
Do you think
he had that story
to tell before today?

825
00:48:48.676 --> 00:48:52.561
I think he was quite credible.

826
00:48:52.630 --> 00:48:56.150
Well. hearing Bryce's name
sure took the attention
away from the school.

827
00:48:56.200 --> 00:48:58.867
Yeah. it's great for us.

828
00:48:58.936 --> 00:49:03.238
These kids. Sonya. teenagers.
they. uh. they have secrets.

829
00:49:04.141 --> 00:49:05.841
They know more than they say.

830
00:49:05.910 --> 00:49:08.354
and they're very good
at telling you the story
you want them to.

831
00:49:08.378 --> 00:49:10.545
I've examined teenagers before.

832
00:49:12.316 --> 00:49:14.756
But you haven't lived with them.

833
00:49:15.285 --> 00:49:18.286
In case you need any advice...
A witness is a witness.

834
00:49:19.389 --> 00:49:21.657
But thanks. Lainie.
I appreciate it.

835
00:49:26.263 --> 00:49:27.263
Good night.

836
00:49:31.119 --> 00:49:33.285
(DOOR OPENING. CLOSING)

837
00:50:09.473 --> 00:50:11.724
MARCUS: <i>Hannah made
a bad decision.</i>

838
00:50:11.792 --> 00:50:14.693
<i>She acted
out of sadness. Anger.</i>

839
00:50:14.762 --> 00:50:16.928
<i>And I just don't want
anyone else to get hurt.</i>

840
00:50:43.407 --> 00:50:45.640
HANNAH: Are you sure
Alex should hear the tapes?

841
00:50:48.379 --> 00:50:51.297
Odd question coming from
the person who made them.

842
00:50:51.365 --> 00:50:54.733
You were trying to protect him.

843
00:50:54.802 --> 00:50:57.837
If he can remember enough.
they might let him testify.

844
00:50:57.905 --> 00:50:59.888
Testify about what?
About Bryce.

845
00:51:00.825 --> 00:51:02.825
The trial's not about Bryce.

846
00:51:03.761 --> 00:51:05.910
Well. it should be.

847
00:51:07.914 --> 00:51:09.381
That girl's unconscious.

848
00:51:10.868 --> 00:51:12.668
You should show these
to someone. Turn him in.

849
00:51:12.719 --> 00:51:13.952
And say what?

850
00:51:14.021 --> 00:51:17.022
"I found this Polaroid
in my locker. arrest him?"

851
00:51:17.091 --> 00:51:19.611
I got his confession
and they did nothing.

852
00:51:20.078 --> 00:51:21.444
Find the girl.

853
00:51:21.512 --> 00:51:22.961
We can't see her face.

854
00:51:23.030 --> 00:51:25.781
Find the room.
The couch is the same
in both pictures.

855
00:51:25.850 --> 00:51:28.095
Nothing I do is going
to make any difference.

856
00:51:28.119 --> 00:51:31.170
Someone has to say
something about Bryce
that makes them pay attention.

857
00:51:31.238 --> 00:51:34.706
Jessica couldn't do it.
they won't let me.
maybe Alex can.

858
00:51:34.775 --> 00:51:37.693
Or maybe it will destroy him
all over again.

859
00:51:38.579 --> 00:51:40.812
Was Marcus lying?

860
00:51:40.882 --> 00:51:44.433
Tell me. If he was lying.
we need someone
to tell the truth.

861
00:51:48.639 --> 00:51:50.872
Things like this are gonna
keep happening. Clay.

862
00:51:53.560 --> 00:51:56.145
You heard my story the way
I wanted it to be told.

863
00:51:56.214 --> 00:51:59.031
but there's always another
side to every story.

864
00:52:00.818 --> 00:52:02.098
How do I know what's true?

865
00:52:04.205 --> 00:52:06.238
You know me. right?

866
00:52:09.109 --> 00:52:10.269
I thought I did.

867
00:52:12.580 --> 00:52:13.913
Then do the right thing.

868
00:52:20.237 --> 00:52:21.237
I am.

869
00:52:41.091 --> 00:52:44.960
MARCUS:<i> But I believe</i>
<i>we're turning a corner.</i>
<i>It's getting better.</i>

870
00:52:52.653 --> 00:52:53.852
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

871
00:53:13.290 --> 00:53:16.524
HANNAH: <i>Hey. It's Hannah.
Hannah Baker.</i>

872
00:53:18.329 --> 00:53:22.130
<i>Don't adjust your...</i>
<i>Whatever device</i>
<i>you're hearing this on.</i>

873
00:53:23.550 --> 00:53:27.152
<i>It's me. live and in stereo.</i>

874
